w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions.png?resize=882,687 882w"></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="show-mobile alignnone wp-image-86941" src="https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png" alt="truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile" width="610" height="998" srcset="https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png 620w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=46,75 46w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=183,300 183w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=313,512 313w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=264,432 264w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=215,352 215w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=138,225 138w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=275,450 275w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=159,260 159w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=98,160 98w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=352,576 352w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=95,155 95w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=61,100 61w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=37,60 37w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=420,687 420w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" data-sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" data-src="https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png" data-srcset="https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png 620w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=46,75 46w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=183,300 183w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=313,512 313w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=264,432 264w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=215,352 215w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=138,225 138w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=275,450 275w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=159,260 159w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=98,160 98w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=352,576 352w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=95,155 95w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=61,100 61w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=37,60 37w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-retractions-mobile.png?resize=420,687 420w"></p>
<p>From 2001 to 2009, the number of retractions issued in the scientific literature <a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2011/111005/full/478026a.html">rose tenfold</a>. It remains a matter of debate whether that’s because misconduct is increasing or is just easier to root out. Fang suspects, based on his experiences as a journal editor, that misconduct has become more common. Others aren’t so sure. “It’s easy to show — <a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosmedicine/article?id=10.1371/journal.pmed.1001563">I’ve done it</a> — that all this growth in retractions is accounted for by the number of new journals that are retracting,” Fanelli said. Still, even with the rise in retractions, fewer than 0.02 percent of publications are retracted annually.</p>
<p>Peer review is supposed to protect against shoddy science, but in November, Oransky, Marcus and Cat Ferguson, then a staff writer at Retraction Watch, uncovered a ring of <a href="http://www.nature.com/news/publishing-the-peer-review-scam-1.16400">fraudulent peer reviewing</a> in which some authors exploited flaws in publishers’ computer systems so they could review their own papers (and those of close colleagues).</p>
<p>Even legitimate peer reviewers let through plenty of errors. Andrew Vickers is the <a href="http://www.europeanurology.com/about/editorial-team/editor/85/andrew-vickers">statistical editor at the journal European Urology</a> and a biostatistician at Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center. A few years back, he decided to write up guidelines for contributors describing common statistical errors and how to avoid them. In preparation for writing the list, he and some colleagues looked back at papers their journal had already published. “We had to go back about 17 papers before we found one without an error,” he told me. His journal isn’t alone — similar problems have turned up, he said, in <a href="http://bja.oxfordjournals.org/content/90/4/514.long">anesthesia</a>, <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2884206/">pain</a>, <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19695587">pediatrics</a> and numerous other types of journals.</p>
<p>Many reviewers just don’t check the methods and statistics sections of a paper, and Arthur Caplan, a medical ethicist at New York University, told me that’s partly because they’re not paid or rewarded for time-consuming peer review work.</p>
<p>Some studies get published with no peer review at all, as so-called “predatory publishers” flood the scientific literature with journals that are essentially fake, publishing any author who pays. Jeffrey Beall, a librarian at the University of Colorado at Denver, has compiled a <a href="http://scholarlyoa.com/publishers/">list of more than 100 so-called “predatory” journal publishers</a>. These journals often have legit-sounding names like the <a href="http://www.wrpjournals.com/journal/international-journal-advanced-chemical-research">International Journal of Advanced Chemical Research</a> and create opportunities for crackpots to give their unscientific views a veneer of legitimacy. (The fake “get me off your fucking mailing list” and “Simpsons” papers were published in such journals.)</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="hide-mobile alignnone wp-image-86876" src="https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png" alt="truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year" width="610" height="495" srcset="https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png 1220w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=92,75 92w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=300,243 300w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=768,623 768w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=1024,831 1024w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=631,512 631w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=532,432 532w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=434,352 434w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=277,225 277w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=555,450 555w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=320,260 320w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=197,160 197w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=710,576 710w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?resize=191,155 191w, https://fivethirtyeight.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/truth-vigilantes-publications-by-year.png?r